{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Xzfu4twbN6y7LmLAQN294h","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have gathered comprehensive information. Let me create a detailed summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary: Tapps-Brain Test Directory Exploration\n\nI've thoroughly explored the tapps-brain test directory and found extensive tests for search/retrieval scoring and trust-related functionality. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **Relevant Test Files for Search/Retrieval Scoring**\n\n#### Unit Tests (Focused, Fast):\n- **/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_source_trust.py** (238 lines)\n  - Tests for `source_trust` multiplier in composite retrieval scoring (M2)\n  - Tests default source trust values (human=1.0, system=0.9, agent=0.7, inferred=0.5)\n  - Tests custom source trust configurations\n  - Tests source trust impact on ranking (human outranks inferred/agent, system outranks agent)\n  - Tests profile YAML loading of source trust config\n  \n- **/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_memory_retrieval.py** (663 lines)\n  - Tests ranked memory retrieval with composite scoring\n  - Tests BM25 integration (Epic 34.2): stemming, IDF scoring, multi-term queries\n  - Tests `ScoredMemory` model creation\n  - Tests confidence, recency, and frequency scoring impacts\n  - Tests reranker integration (Epic 65.9)\n  - Tests temporal filtering and superseded entries\n  - Tests fallback mechanisms (word overlap, LIKE search)\n  - Comprehensive scoring helper tests (`_normalize_relevance`, `_recency_score`, `_frequency_score`)\n\n- **/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_memory_bm25.py** (200+ lines)\n  - Tests for BM25 scoring engine\n  - Tests stemming (`stem()` function)\n  - Tests preprocessing (`preprocess()` function)\n  - Tests stop words handling\n\n#### Integration Tests (Real SQLite, FTS5, Real Decay):\n- **/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/integration/test_retrieval_integration.py** (549 lines)\n  - End-to-end tests with real MemoryStore + SQLite\n  - Tests BM25 with real FTS5 (test_exact_keyword_match_ranks_highest)\n  - Tests contradicted entry exclusion (by default and with flags)\n  - Tests consolidated source entries\n  - Tests decayed/stale entries ranking lower\n  - Tests decay by tier (architectural vs context)\n  - Tests min_confidence filtering\n  - Tests frequency boost (access_count)\n  - Tests composite scoring integration with real store\n  - Tests hybrid search fallback paths\n  - Validates all scoring fields are populated\n\n- **/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/integration/test_recall_integration.py**\n  - Integration tests for auto-recall round-trip with real MemoryStore\n\n### 2. **Test Structure and Patterns**\n\n#### Test Organization:\n```\ntests/\n├── conftest.py              # Shared pytest fixtures\n├── factories.py             # make_entry() factory for all test variants\n├── unit/                    # Fast, isolated unit tests (71 files)\n│   ├── test_source_trust.py\n│   ├── test_memory_retrieval.py\n│   ├── test_memory_bm25.py\n│   ├── test_memory_decay.py\n│   ├── test_memory_store.py\n│   └── ... (59 more)\n├── integration/             # Real store tests (17 files)\n│   ├── test_retrieval_integration.py\n│   ├── test_recall_integration.py\n│   └── ...\n└── benchmarks/\n```\n\n#### Key Test Patterns:\n\n**1. Mock Helper Pattern** (`_make_entry`, `_make_store`):\n```python\ndef _make_entry(\n    key: str = \"test-key\",\n    value: str = \"test value\",\n    *,\n    confidence: float = 0.8,\n    source: MemorySource = MemorySource.agent,\n    access_count: int = 5,\n) -> MemoryEntry:\n    return make_entry(...)\n\ndef _make_store(entries: list[MemoryEntry]) -> MagicMock:\n    store = MagicMock()\n    store.list_all.return_value = entries\n    store.search.return_value = entries\n    entry_map = {e.key: e for e in entries}\n    store.get.side_effect = lambda k, **kwargs: entry_map.get(k)\n    return store\n```\n\n**2. Central Factory Pattern** (`tests/factories.py`):\n- Single `make_entry()` function with 20+ parameters\n- Defaults to UTC now for timestamps\n- Confidence default of -1.0 triggers model's source-based defaults\n- Used throughout all test files\n\n**3. Test Class Organization**:\n- Group related tests by feature/component (e.g., `TestSourceTrustRanking`, `TestBM25Integration`)\n- Each class tests one specific aspect\n- Methods prefixed with `test_` following pytest conventions\n\n**4. Real Store Integration Tests**:\n```python\n@pytest.fixture()\ndef store(tmp_path: Path) -> MemoryStore:\n    s = MemoryStore(tmp_path)\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef _save(store, key, value, *, tier=\"pattern\", tags=None, confidence=-1.0, source=\"agent\"):\n    result = store.save(...)\n    assert not isinstance(result, dict), f\"save failed: {result}\"\n```\n\n**5. Assertion Patterns**:\n- Direct equality checks for keys, sources\n- Score comparisons (>, <, approx)\n- Score bounds validation (0.0 ≤ score ≤ 1.0)\n- Ranking order validation using keys/indices\n- Result length validation (len(results) == N)\n\n### 3. **Pytest Configuration**\n\nLocated in `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/pyproject.toml`:\n- **testpaths**: `[\"tests\"]`\n- **asyncio_mode**: `auto`\n- **Markers**:\n  - `@pytest.mark.benchmark` — performance benchmarks\n  - `@pytest.mark.requires_cli` — tests needing [cli] extra (typer)\n  - `@pytest.mark.requires_mcp` — tests needing [mcp] extra\n\n### 4. **Source Trust Tests Summary**\n\nThe **test_source_trust.py** file tests the M2 (source trust multiplier) feature with three main test classes:\n\n1. **TestScoringConfigSourceTrust** (4 tests)\n   - Default trust values assertion\n   - Custom trust acceptance\n   - Weight sum unaffected by multiplier\n   - Default consistency across modules\n\n2. **TestRetrieverSourceTrust** (3 tests)\n   - Retriever loads default source trust\n   - Retriever respects ScoringConfig.source_trust\n   - Bare configs without source_trust fall back to defaults\n\n3. **TestSourceTrustRanking** (7 tests)\n   - human > inferred ordering\n   - human > agent ordering  \n   - system > agent ordering\n   - All four sources ranked: human → system → agent → inferred\n   - Custom trust can reverse default ordering\n   - Unknown sources default to trust=1.0 (no penalty)\n   - Trust=1.0 is identity multiplier (preserves original score)\n\n### 5. **Related Source Files**\n\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py` — MemoryRetriever implementation\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/bm25.py` — BM25Scorer and stemming/preprocessing\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/reranker.py` — Reranking logic\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profile.py` — ScoringConfig with source_trust field\n\n### 6. **Coverage and Quality**\n\n- **Unit tests**: 71 test files covering all major modules\n- **Integration tests**: 17 test files with real stores and SQLite\n- **Test count**: 1000+ tests across both unit and integration\n- **Key coverage areas**:\n  - Composite scoring (relevance, confidence, recency, frequency)\n  - BM25 and stemming\n  - Source trust multiplier\n  - Temporal filtering and decay\n  - Reranking integration\n  - Fallback mechanisms\n  - Real SQLite/FTS5 end-to-end paths\n\nThis codebase demonstrates professional test practices with clear patterns for creating fixtures, organizing tests, and validating ranking/scoring behavior both in isolation and with real data stores."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1499c428a8499ed8 (use SendMessage with to: 'a1499c428a8499ed8' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 67438\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 56026</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4c2bbd2a-1a06-4e1e-9000-d7a8b9bf3b8b","uuid":"362febd1-2c79-4f46-8de8-8b010d0f8db6","timestamp":"2026-03-22T22:47:39.575Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the tapps-brain test directory at /mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/ to find:\n1. Existing tests for