 entry_map = {e.key: e for e in entries}\n    store.get.side_effect = lambda k, **kwargs: entry_map.get(k)\n    return store\n```\n\n**2. Central Factory Pattern** (`tests/factories.py`):\n- Single `make_entry()` function with 20+ parameters\n- Defaults to UTC now for timestamps\n- Confidence default of -1.0 triggers model's source-based defaults\n- Used throughout all test files\n\n**3. Test Class Organization**:\n- Group related tests by feature/component (e.g., `TestSourceTrustRanking`, `TestBM25Integration`)\n- Each class tests one specific aspect\n- Methods prefixed with `test_` following pytest conventions\n\n**4. Real Store Integration Tests**:\n```python\n@pytest.fixture()\ndef store(tmp_path: Path) -> MemoryStore:\n    s = MemoryStore(tmp_path)\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\ndef _save(store, key, value, *, tier=\"pattern\", tags=None, confidence=-1.0, source=\"agent\"):\n    result = store.save(...)\n    assert not isinstance(result, dict), f\"save failed: {result}\"\n```\n\n**5. Assertion Patterns**:\n- Direct equality checks for keys, sources\n- Score comparisons (>, <, approx)\n- Score bounds validation (0.0 ≤ score ≤ 1.0)\n- Ranking order validation using keys/indices\n- Result length validation (len(results) == N)\n\n### 3. **Pytest Configuration**\n\nLocated in `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/pyproject.toml`:\n- **testpaths**: `[\"tests\"]`\n- **asyncio_mode**: `auto`\n- **Markers**:\n  - `@pytest.mark.benchmark` — performance benchmarks\n  - `@pytest.mark.requires_cli` — tests needing [cli] extra (typer)\n  - `@pytest.mark.requires_mcp` — tests needing [mcp] extra\n\n### 4. **Source Trust Tests Summary**\n\nThe **test_source_trust.py** file tests the M2 (source trust multiplier) feature with three main test classes:\n\n1. **TestScoringConfigSourceTrust** (4 tests)\n   - Default trust values assertion\n   - Custom trust acceptance\n   - Weight sum unaffected by multiplier\n   - Default consistency across modules\n\n2. **TestRetrieverSourceTrust** (3 tests)\n   - Retriever loads default source trust\n   - Retriever respects ScoringConfig.source_trust\n   - Bare configs without source_trust fall back to defaults\n\n3. **TestSourceTrustRanking** (7 tests)\n   - human > inferred ordering\n   - human > agent ordering  \n   - system > agent ordering\n   - All four sources ranked: human → system → agent → inferred\n   - Custom trust can reverse default ordering\n   - Unknown sources default to trust=1.0 (no penalty)\n   - Trust=1.0 is identity multiplier (preserves original score)\n\n### 5. **Related Source Files**\n\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/retrieval.py` — MemoryRetriever implementation\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/bm25.py` — BM25Scorer and stemming/preprocessing\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/reranker.py` — Reranking logic\n- `/mnt/c/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profile.py` — ScoringConfig with source_trust field\n\n### 6. **Coverage and Quality**\n\n- **Unit tests**: 71 test files covering all major modules\n- **Integration tests**: 17 test files with real stores and SQLite\n- **Test count**: 1000+ tests across both unit and integration\n- **Key coverage areas**:\n  - Composite scoring (relevance, confidence, recency, frequency)\n  - BM25 and stemming\n  - Source trust multiplier\n  - Temporal filtering and decay\n  - Reranking integration\n  - Fallback mechanisms\n  - Real SQLite/FTS5 end-to-end paths\n\nThis codebase demonstrates professional test practices with clear patterns for creating fixtures, organizing tests, and validating ranking/scoring behavior both in isolation and with real data stores."}],"totalDurationMs":56026,"totalTokens":67438,"totalToolUseCount":17,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":271,"cache_read_input_tokens":65003,"output_tokens":2164,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":271},"inference